# Plan Eval — KS Global Estates

## Rubric Evaluation

### 1. Requirement Coverage (all 11 R# from brief.json)

| R# | Requirement | Plan Coverage | Status |
|----|-------------|---------------|--------|
| R1 | Frontend + backend website | Vite+React frontend + `properties.js` as client-side data layer (mock backend). Proposal narrative addresses architecture. | PASS |
| R2 | Visually appealing, brand-communicating design | Full bespoke design system: #12100E/#F5F1EB/#B8975A palette, Cormorant Garamond + DM Sans, editorial asymmetric layout, specified down to `letter-spacing` and `line-height`. | PASS |
| R3 | User-friendly interface | Split-pane with sticky FilterPanel, keyboard-accessible inputs, responsive layout noted in traceability, scroll sync on list/map interaction. | PASS (minor: mobile breakpoint left to builder — acceptable) |
| R4 | High-quality portfolio work | 13 named files, clean component structure, zero-console-error goal, Leaflet scaffold from proven mn-state-park-tracker baseline. | PASS |
| R5 | Reasonable timeframe and budget | Proposal narrative only (no demo coverage). Acceptable — this is a business communication point, not a technical feature. | PASS |
| R6 | Property listing / browsing | PropertyList with sortable, filterable, searchable cards; live filter state in App.jsx passed to both panels. | PASS |
| R7 | Mock DB (houses, condos, estates) | `properties.js`: 25 properties spanning houses, condos, penthouses, villas, estates across 10+ global cities. Schema specified. | PASS |
| R8 | List view | PropertyList panel; card click opens PropertyDetail modal with gallery, specs, inquiry form, favorites toggle. | PASS |
| R9 | Map view with map technology | Leaflet 1.9.4 + CARTO Voyager tiles, custom DivIcon price pins, `flyTo`, pin/list two-way sync. Direct pattern from mn-state-park-tracker. | PASS |
